  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI have a project that connects to oracle db using the jdbc-oracle extension.\r\nWhen I connect to a oracle db with UTF8 charset everything works.\r\nIf I use an oracle db with a different charset (for instance JA16SJIS) the application hangs with the following exception:\r\n`java.sql.SQLException: Non supported character set (add orai18n.jar in your classpath)`\r\n\r\nTo fix the issue I added explicitly the following dependency\r\n`runtimeOnly group: 'com.oracle.database.nls', name: 'orai18n', version: '21.3.0.0'`\r\n\r\nIn my opinion would be better to add this dependency directly to the jdbc-oracle extension, to avoid versions mismatch between jdbc connector and the orai18n jar.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe application should work with oracle db with charset different from UTF-8.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe application hangs with the following exception:\r\n`java.sql.SQLException: Non supported character set (add orai18n.jar in your classpath)`\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nOpenJDK Runtime Environment AdoptOpenJDK (build 11.0.9+11)\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.6.1.Final\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
